ATTRIBUTIONS / LINEAGE (this benchmark deliberately builds on recognized prior art):

- Result comparator (harness/comparator.py) reimplements the semantics of Spider's
  `test-suite-sql-eval` `result_eq` / `eval_exec_match`
  (https://github.com/taoyds/test-suite-sql-eval, Apache-2.0). See docs/REUSE.md.

- Metric design follows the published lineage: execution accuracy (Spider/BIRD),
  table-retrieval recall/F1 (BEAVER), and set-recall@k (RASL/LinkAlign, 2025).
  See docs/METHODOLOGY.md and docs/RELATED-WORK.md for citations.

- The schema mirrors the SHAPE of recognized open-source production schemas (Saleor,
  Medusa, Kill Bill, Stripe data model, Chatwoot, Snowplow, Keycloak, ...). No GPL/AGPL
  DDL is copied; only conceptual structure is echoed. Per-domain provenance and licenses:
  docs/SCHEMA-PROVENANCE.md.

- Data generation uses Mimesis (MIT) for string pools and NumPy for all randomness.
  TPC-H/TPC-DS skew ideas are re-implemented, not shipped (TPC tools are under a
  restrictive EULA — never bundled). See seed/DATA-REALISM.md.
